Description: Implement OFAC geo-blocking and sanctioned address blocking

Geo-blocking via Next.js Middleware:
```ts
// middleware.ts
import { NextResponse } from 'next/server';

const BLOCKED_COUNTRIES = ['CU', 'IR', 'SY', 'KP', 'RU'];

export function middleware(request) {
  const country = request.geo?.country;
  if (BLOCKED_COUNTRIES.includes(country)) {
    return NextResponse.redirect(new URL('/blocked', request.url));
  }
}
```

Sanctioned Address Blocking:
- Maintain blocked addresses in Set:
```ts
export const BLOCKED_ADDRESSES = new Set(['0x1234...abcd', '0xdead...beef']);

export const isAddressSanctioned = (address: string) =>
  BLOCKED_ADDRESSES.has(address.toLowerCase());
```

Check at swap initiation or wallet connect:
```ts
if (isAddressSanctioned(userAddress)) {
  toast.error('This address is blocked from using the service.');
  return;
}
```

User Experience:
- Clearly inform via redirect (`/blocked`) or toast/error message.
- Prevent further interaction if sanctioned.
